## Folder structure
```
.
├── public/
│   └── images/               # placeholder image slots (replace before launch)
├── src/
│   ├── components/           # reusable UI blocks
│   ├── data/                 # editable copy/content and schema helpers
│   ├── layouts/              # page wrapper layout
│   ├── pages/                # all routes
│   └── styles/               # global design system CSS
├── astro.config.mjs
├── package.json
└── REDESIGN_NOTES.md
```

## Image placeholder system
All current visuals are **text-based SVG placeholders** so the PR stays binary-free and fully reviewable.
The following image paths are already wired into components/pages:
- `/public/images/hero-hydroseeding.svg`
- `/public/images/large-lawn-installation.svg`
- `/public/images/commercial-erosion-control.svg`
- `/public/images/new-construction-lawn.svg`
- `/public/images/lawn-maintenance.svg`
- `/public/images/soil-prep.svg`
- `/public/images/before-lawn-1.svg`
- `/public/images/after-lawn-1.svg`
- `/public/images/before-lawn-2.svg`
- `/public/images/after-lawn-2.svg`
- `/public/images/equipment-process.svg`
- `/public/images/contact-quote.svg`

### Replacing placeholder images
1. Keep the same filenames to avoid updating component references.
2. Replace files with approved real photos (`.jpg`, `.webp`, etc.) or production SVG artwork while keeping the same filenames/paths as needed.
3. Preserve/adjust `alt` text in components for accessibility and local SEO context.
4. Ensure all real images are licensed and approved by the business.

## SEO improvements included
- Unique page titles and descriptions.
- Semantic heading structure.
- Local-intent internal links between service and location pages.
- FAQ content on homepage and detail pages.
- JSON-LD support for LocalBusiness, Service, and FAQPage.
- Sitemap route (`/sitemap.xml`) and robots route (`/robots.txt`).
- Natural keyword integration (no stuffing).

## Quote form integration options (currently frontend-only)
The form is intentionally backend-free in this demo. You can connect it via:

### Netlify Forms
- Add `name="quote"` and `data-netlify="true"` on `<form>`.
- Include hidden `<input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="quote" />`.

### Formspree
- Set `action="https://formspree.io/f/{your-id}"` and `method="POST"`.

### EmailJS
- Add client-side script with EmailJS SDK and map fields to template variables.

### Resend or custom API route
- Add server endpoint (Astro API route) and send validated payload to email service.

## Install and run
> Note: if your environment blocks npm registry access, install commands may fail until network policy is updated.

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

Open local URL shown by Astro (usually `http://localhost:4321`).

## Build
```bash
npm run build
npm run preview
```

## Deploy to Vercel
1. Push repo to GitHub.
2. Import project in Vercel.
3. Build command: `npm run build`
4. Output directory: `dist`
5. Deploy.

## Replit usage
1. Import repo into Replit.
2. Run `npm install`.
3. Set run command to `npm run dev -- --host`.
4. Use Replit webview URL for preview.

## Presenting this demo respectfully (Tobin Studio guidance)
- Frame as a **capability demo**, not criticism.
- Acknowledge existing site strengths first.
- Emphasize gains in conversion clarity, local SEO structure, and service-page depth.
- Offer migration in phases (copy, photos, trust assets, form backend).
- Keep testimonial/review data factual and owner-approved.
